    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "What form do you see this taking? Currently, you can (and we often do) override the capabilities from nvim-lspconfig. In fact, these completely ovewrite the default client capabilities generated by `vim.lsp.protocol. protocol.make_client_capabilities()` https://github.com/mjlbach/neovim/blob/f87ae324bb03ccd9f723a6b2a664e6058849f0f7/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua#L632.\r\n\r\nCurrently a plugin could override the default capabilities in nvim-lspconfig, which would therefore set the capabilities in core. Is there something particular about how this is managed in core that you thing should change?",
            "created_at": "2021-04-01T07:08:47Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12833#issuecomment-811697329",
